Cell.Text: [S] S|I remember you... You were at Helgen with us! Come to join the war? Speak with Galmar. He handles the new recruits.
S|[E] Only the foolish or the courageous approach a Jarl without summons... | Do I know you?
[E] As you can see, I have much that requires my attention. If you're inclined to gab, there are some nice prison guards you may like to meet...
Is that so...? | Ah yes, you were with us at Helgen.
Ahhh. Yes...

Cell.Text: A fair point... Well, you've come to the right place, then. Speak with Galmar.

Node.Caption: CW00BUlfricGreetFreeToGo: I was set free. I could've gone anywhere. I came here to fight the Empire.

Cell.Text: Destined for the chopping block if I'm not mistaken.

[S] G|[E] I'm always looking for able fighters. Not everyone can say they made it out of Helgen. | Seems we're all branded villains these days... | So long as your criminal past stays in the past, and you fight for me with honor and integrity, we'll welcome you into our ranks.
[S] G|I'm not sure you belong here, friend.
Hmm. Helgen, eh? Ulfric told us quite the story. If you made it through all that, you're likely worth something to me.
About that test...
Are you ready to for Serpentstone Island?
[S] [E] That's what I like to hear. | So long as you can back up those words with steel.

Node.Caption: CW00BGalmarHandleAnything: I can handle anything you throw at me.

Cell.Text: The kind men use to measure themselves.

It's where men have tested their mettle for ages. | [E] There's a strange rock formation, built by the ancients. Something about that place attracts the Ice Wraiths. | You kill an Ice Wraith out there, and I'll have all the proof I need about you.
I'm sending you to Serpentstone Island. If you survive, you pass. If you die, well, you weren't going to be much use to me anyway.
S|Not so sure of yourself after all?
At the end of the day, every warrior is alone. | Before you can stand next to your shield brother, you need to be able to stand on your own.
[S] G|When you kill that Ice Wraith, then we'll talk about you becoming a Stormcloak.

[S] G|When you kill that Ice Wraith, then we'll talk about you becoming a Stormcloak. | Here. Take this. You'll need it. Use it on the island. Don't lose it. That's all the help you're getting. | Try not to die.

Node.Caption: CW00BGalmarAcceptQuest: I'm off to kill that Ice Wraith. I'll be back soon.

Cell.Text: Ralof's alive? I hope that's true. He's a damn good man. | But he hasn't returned yet, so I'll need to wait for his account. For now, speak with Galmar.

Node.Caption: CW00BUlfricGreetRalof: I helped Ralof escape. He said he'd vouch for me.

Cell.Text: But first, tell me. Why's an Elf want to fight for Skyrim?
But first, tell me. Why's a cat want to fight for Skyrim?
But first, tell me. Why's a lizard want to fight for Skyrim?
But first, tell me. Why's an Orc want to fight for Skyrim?
But first, tell me. Why's a Redguard want to fight for Skyrim?
But first, tell me. Why's a Breton want to fight for Skyrim?
But first, tell me. Why's a foreigner want to fight for Skyrim?

[E] You mistake me. I'm not saying no - just wondering about your intentions. | [E] We're not looking for sellswords. The Stormcloaks need dedicated men and women who're devoted to the cause and willing to die for it.
Skyrim is home to more than just Nords.
<<Shared>> Fair enough. But are you willing to die for your home?
Skyrim is my home.
<<Shared>> Fair enough. But are you willing to die for your home?
Can't fault anyone for that! As long as you hate the Empire as much as I do, that I can work with.

Node.Caption: CW00BGalmarFightEmpire: I want to fight the Empire. I'll bleed for the chance to do so.

Cell.Text: [S] All right. But before I can put you to use, I need to know how much you can take. I have a little test for you.

Node.Caption: CW00BGalmarSignMeUp: That's why I'm here. I want to join.

Cell.Text: Only the ones I'm not sure about. This will prove your abilities, but more importantly, it will prove your commitment.

Node.Caption: CW00BGalmarEveryoneDoThis: Does every recruit have to do this?

Cell.Text: G|Good.
G|I'm sorry to hear that. If you change your mind, speak with Galmar. Now, if you'll excuse me...
